cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the application of deep learning models for clinical text classification and keyword extraction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also uses attention-based models, which are a popular technique in deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of BERT, a pre-trained language model, also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. The paper also deals with information retrieval and classification, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) respectively.
